# Secure Boot: the signed shim is what makes the image bootable with Secure Boot
# enabled (shim -> grub2 -> kernel, all signed by Fedora's keys). The base usually
# ships it, but pin it so the guarantee does not depend on the base. Enabling
# Secure Boot itself is a UEFI firmware action, not a build step.
shim-x64
grub2-efi-x64
